KEY TAKEAWAYS FOR MERE MORTALS: 

Browsers are now full operating systems and deserve the same caution as any critical application.
JavaScript engines are incredibly complex and can become powerful attack surfaces. Browser extensions are the new Trojan horses, 
and users should install very few of them. Automatic updates are essential for security but also a potential attack vector. 
Modern attacks are often completely invisible. Good security hygiene still matters: unique random passwords,
minimal extensions, staying updated, and being mindful of which companies you trust with your data. Most importantly, 
attackers and companies can only misuse the data you choose to provide. Separating your online identity from your real one limits what can be taken from you. 
